==Lifeline Assistance free government operators (California and Minnesota)==
The following is a list of the mobile virtual network operators offering government subsidized [[Universal Service Fund#Low income (Lifeline)|Lifeline]] mobile services in '''California''' and '''Minnesota'''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.freegovernmentcellphones.net/states/california-government-cell-phone-providers|title=California Lifeline: Free Cell Phones with Unlimited Talk/Text|website=www.freegovernmentcellphones.net|access-date=2016-11-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.freegovernmentcellphones.net/cdma-gsm-lte-phone-compatible-with-my-free-phone-network|title=Is any phone compatible with my free phone network?|website=www.freegovernmentcellphones.net|language=en-US|access-date=2017-03-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.prepaid-wireless-guide.com/lifeline-providers.html|title=Lifeline Providers|work=Prepaid Wireless Guide|access-date=2017-03-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://motodevelopers.org/get-fake-number-whatsapp-account/|title={3 Methods} How to get a fake number for WhatsApp account|date=2017-12-20|work=Moto Developers|access-date=2018-01-02|language=en-GB}}</ref> This list needs to be expanded for all other states. All 50 States run and operate their own Lifeline programs so company, MVNOs participation and plan offerings vary greatly from state to state.

